rdf:Description.fullName: HLA class I histocompatibility antigen, A-1 alpha chain

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Involved in the presentation of foreign antigens to the immune system.
Dimer of alpha chain and a beta chain (beta-2-microglobulin). Interacts with human herpesvirus 8 MIR1 protein (By similarity).
Polyubiquitinated in a post ER compartment through interaction with human herpesvirus 8 MIR1 protein. This targets the protein for rapid degradation via the ubiquitin system (By similarity).
The following alleles of A-1 are known: A*01:01, A*01:02, A*01:03, A*01:06 and A*01:07. The sequence shown is that of A*01:01.
Belongs to the MHC class I family.
